---
import ScrollReveal from "./ScrollReveal.tsx";
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
---

<section id="services" class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 py-20">
	<!--<ScrollReveal client:idle delay={0.1}>
		<h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 text-center mb-12">Services</h2>
	</ScrollReveal>-->

	<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
		<ScrollReveal client:idle delay={0.2} scale={true}>
			<div
				class="block p-6 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow"
			>
				<div
					class="w-12 h-12 bg-gray-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
				>
					<Icon
						name="tabler:lock"
						class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-900"
						aria-hidden="true"
					/>
				</div>
				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">
					Security & Hardening
				</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-600">
					Security isn’t a checkbox — it’s a continuous and evolving practice.
					From configuring servers and services to be secure by default, to
					hardening network interfaces, and utilizing tools to reduce risk and
					detect vulnerabilities. Secure server and network
					configuration, basic penetration testing and vulnerability scanning,
					web & API service hardening, SSL/TLS configuration and automation, and
					guidance on ongoing security practices.
				</p>
			</div>
		</ScrollReveal>

		<ScrollReveal client:idle delay={0.3} scale={true}>
			<div
				class="block p-6 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow"
			>
				<div
					class="w-12 h-12 bg-gray-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
				>
					<Icon
						name="tabler:blocks"
						class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-900"
						aria-hidden="true"
					/>
				</div>
				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">
					Builds & Continuous Integration (CI)
				</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-600">
					I help teams set up reliable, automated build pipelines that run tests
					and checks on every change, produce dependable artifacts, that reduce
					manual errors. Tools I commonly work with are GitHub Actions, Jenkins
					(CloudBees), and Azure CI/CD. These pipelines improve confidence in
					your software and speed up delivery.
					<br /><br /><br />
				</p>
			</div>
		</ScrollReveal>

		<ScrollReveal client:idle delay={0.4} scale={true}>
			<div
				class="p-6 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow"
			>
				<div
					class="w-12 h-12 bg-gray-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
				>
					<Icon
						name="tabler:brand-docker"
						class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-900"
						aria-hidden="true"
					/>
				</div>
				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">
					Containerization with Docker
				</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-600">
					Containerization brings flexibility and consistency across
					environments. I can help convert and package applications in Docker
					containers to create reproducible infrastructure, which uses the
					Infrastructure as Code (IaC) ideals for scalable and reproduceable
					deployments. This leads to easier testing, more predictable
					deployments with better infrastructure visibility since all the code
					is open and readable.
					<br /><br />
				</p>
			</div>
		</ScrollReveal>

		<ScrollReveal client:idle delay={0.7} scale={true}>
			<div
				class="p-6 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow"
			>
				<div
					class="w-12 h-12 bg-gray-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
				>
					<Icon
						name="tabler:brand-ansible"
						class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-900"
						se
						aria-hidden="true"
					/>
				</div>
				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">
					Infrastructure as Code with Ansible
				</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-600">
					Manual server setup invites mistakes. Using Ansible, I define
					infrastructure declaratively so that configurations are repeatable and
					thus reproduceable, documentation becomes inherent in the code itself
					and the rollouts are reliable. This approach ensures systems stay in
					sync and they become immutable, only changed via Ansible runs.
				</p>
			</div>
		</ScrollReveal>

		<ScrollReveal client:idle delay={0.5} scale={true}>
			<div
				class="p-6 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow"
			>
				<div
					class="w-12 h-12 bg-gray-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
				>
					<Icon
						name="tabler:certificate"
						class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-900"
						aria-hidden="true"
					/>
				</div>
				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">
					SSL Certificates
				</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-600">
					Secure Web Traffic with confidence, I can setup and automate SSL/TLS
					certificate issuance from online providers. This involves implementing
					Let’s Encrypt for automation, which ensures the idea of HTTPS
					everywhere. Proper certificates not only protect data in transit, they
					build trust with users while making the Ineternet safer for everyone.
				</p>
			</div>
		</ScrollReveal>

		<ScrollReveal client:idle delay={0.6} scale={true}>
			<div
				class="p-6 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow"
			>
				<div
					class="w-12 h-12 bg-gray-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
				>
					<Icon
						name="tabler:file-text"
						class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-900"
						aria-hidden="true"
					/>
				</div>
				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">
					Documentation & Strategy
				</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-600">
					Good documentation turns knowledge into an asset. I include clear
					documentation with every engagement so you always know how the systems
					are built, how things are configured, and how to updates and
					migrations occur in order to maintain or extend your infrastructure.
					I've always shared knowledge in an open, and accessible way.
				</p>
			</div>
		</ScrollReveal>

		<ScrollReveal client:idle delay={0.8} scale={true}>
			<div
				class="p-6 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow"
			>
				<div
					class="w-12 h-12 bg-gray-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
				>
					<Icon
						name="tabler:seo"
						class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-900"
						aria-hidden="true"
					/>
				</div>
				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">SEO</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-600">
					Search engine optimization (SEO) is important so that your website and
					information can be discovered by Google and other search providers.
					There are some basic steps to take, and most web frameworks include a
					lot of bits already, but it's always good to review and update
					settings to be up to date.
					<br /><br />
				</p>
			</div>
		</ScrollReveal>

		<ScrollReveal client:idle delay={0.9} scale={true}>
			<div
				class="block p-6 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow"
			>
				<div
					class="w-12 h-12 bg-gray-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
				>
					<Icon
						name="tabler:brand-windows"
						class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-900"
						aria-hidden="true"
					/>
				</div>
				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Windows</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-600">
					While most people think running Windows, or systems that utilize
					proprietary software, makes using open source a foreign concept,
					that's not true. Early I learned how to run
					the Apache webserver in Windows and an alternative to Microsoft's own IIS. Applying these concepts to
					Windows provides a more controlled, and secured environment.
				</p>
			</div>
		</ScrollReveal>

		<ScrollReveal client:idle delay={1.0} scale={true}>
			<div
				class="block p-6 bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow"
			>
				<div
					class="w-12 h-12 bg-gray-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
				>
					<Icon
						name="tabler:exclamation-circle"
						class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-900"
						aria-hidden="true"
					/>
				</div>
				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">
					Custom Solutions
				</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-600">
					But wait,there's more... no two problems are the same, so if you have a specific challenge not listed here, let’s talk — I enjoy breaking down problems and building tailored solutions that fit your context. I'm cognizant of the fact that there are virtually infinite ways to solve technical issues, and I enjoy figuring those out to help clients achieve their goals.
				</p>
			</div>
		</ScrollReveal>
	</div>
</section>
